Tony: Uh, eleven, eleven and a half.
Steve: Great, because my shoes are giving me a little...
body:
Steve: What size shoes do you wear?

Tony: Uh, eleven, eleven and a half.

Steve: Great, because my shoes are giving me a little problem on the dance floor, can I borrow the boots?

Tony: Uh, I don’t even really know where I left those. Sorry.

Steve: [looks at Tony’s feet] Those aren’t eleven and a half.

Tony: Okay fine! I’m a seven! All right, I have surprisingly small feet. But the rest of me is good, I’ll show ya!

summary: “I used to have thoughts of wanting to climb to the top of something, or wanting to be somebody,” he said. “But when you get the...
caption: “I used to have thoughts of wanting to climb to the top of something, or wanting to be somebody,” he said. “But when you get the thing that you think you want and then you wake up and realize that you still have pockets of sadness, and that your struggle will reinvent itself, you stop chasing after those things and it’s liberating, because you realize that right here, right now, is exactly all I need.”

Ryan Coogler Set To Return For Black Panther 2

tags: :') i just had to let it out
summary:
Lemme just say it...
I can't be the only one who finds it hard to let go of the goodest and the bravest Captain Steve Rogers :')...
body:
Lemme just say it…

I can’t be the only one who finds it hard to let go of the goodest and the bravest Captain Steve Rogers :’) I still remember the time i got into the fandom back in 2014 a blink and woosh! It’s 2018 already. It’s not just Steve Rogers in general but also Chris Evans…I literally cannot see anyone else playing the character better than him and I just wanna thank him for all his hard work he put into the character all these years :’) as much as it hurts to see him leave the role, I thank him for not only for his work but also the kindness and memories he has given to the fandom.

Love you man! You’ll forever be our Captain💖
